<p id="subhead">
    <!-- Type tribute info here-->
    <h2>This page is a tribute for the song '<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tribute_(song)" target="_blank" id="tribute-link">Tribute</a>'. 'Tribute' was written to honor to The Best Song In The World, a song that was created on the spot and used to win a musical duel with the devil.</h2>
</p>
<p id="tribute-info">
Musicians <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jack_Black" target="_blank">Jack Black</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyle_Gass" target="_blank">Kyle Gass</a> form the super-talented duo Tenacious D.
<br>
A long time ago, Black and his brother Kyle there were hitchhiking down a long and lonesome road.
All of a sudden there shined a shiny demon <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dave_Grohl" target="_blank">(Dave Grohl)</a> in the middle of the road.
He said "Play the best song in the world or I'll eat your soul."
Jack and Kyle looked at each other, and each one said "Okay." 
They played the first thing that came to their heads, and it just so happened to be the best song in the world.
</p>

<br>

